sentence: The Dynamic Building & Construction Portfolio ETF ( PKB ) is seeing unusually high volume in afternoon trading Wednesday, with over 191,000 shares traded versus three month average volume of about 44,000.
Shares of PKB were down about 0.2% on the day.

Components of that ETF with the highest volume on Wednesday were KBR ( KBR ), trading up about 0.6% with over 2.7 million shares changing hands so far this session, and Home Depot ( HD ), off about 0.1% on volume of over 2.7 million shares.

URS ( URS ) is the component faring the best Wednesday, higher by about 1.5% on the day, while The Manitowoc Company ( MTW ) is lagging other components of the Dynamic Building & Construction Portfolio ETF, trading lower by about 2%.
